the truck cab to turn off the engine when the blast hit 
officials said a volunteer firefighter who lives near the plains 
oil office jeff hunker dragged the driver away from the flames 
the fire visible up to five miles away was so hot that 
firefighters had to wait 45 minutes before they could begin 
battling it the crews trained hoses on gasoline storage tanks to 
keep them from exploding 
the fire spread to the plains oil office and burned it to the 
ground the truck cab and tank melted officials said 
authorities evacuated a nearby park officials said 
the tanker truck driver was in critical condition and was to be 
