automated safety system could shut the platform down 
we had sensors which would have detected ordinary leaks and 
would have given us warning but this explosion was so tremendous 
that no sensors would operate there hammer told the news 
conference 
david martin president of occidental oil and gas corp the 
subsidiary which operates the rig said in aberdeen he had no 
confirmation of any leaks prior to wednesdays explosion but was 
aware of reports that some workers had smelled gas 
adair 73 and two assistants had to postpone plans to board the 
platform when winds of 35 mph buffeted the site said an occidental 
spokeswoman who would not give her name adair has worked on the 
site since friday and must clear the platform of debris to gain 
access to the wellheads and seal them 
about 30 percent of the debris has been cleared 
the spokeswoman said the houston disaster specialist and his 
team returned to their base on the semisubmersible service vessel 
tharos 
it was the second time in two days that adairs efforts to work 
on the platform were frustrated he was forced to cancel a visit at 
dawn sunday because of heavy seas high winds and flames shooting 
into the air from one of the three wellheads still burning 
in red deer alberta a canadian who was a former platform 
superintendent on the rig was quoted on monday as saying the piper 
alpha rig was a bomb waiting to explode 
i was glad to get off that thing ralph miller of red deer 
was quoted as saying by the canadian press news agency 
miller who worked on the rig from 198082 said the problem 
stemmed from the rigs productivity according to the news agency 
the piper alpha rig was one of the best producers at 120000 
barrels of oil a day and one of the most profitable in the british 
section of the north sea 
miller was quoted as saying that pressure to keep the oil 
flowing led to lax maintenance with valves sometimes not turning 
and an inch or more of grease on some of the working decks 
basically it went down to neglect they had safety meetings 
but how much did it help miller was quoted as saying 
