agencys factual findings about a veterans claim 
the senatepassed bill would permit a court to overturn an 
adverse finding by the vas board of veterans appeals only when 
the court finds the decision so utterly lacking in a rational 
basis in the evidence that a manifest and grievous injustice would 
result if such finding were not set aside 
