<TEXT>
after more than 400 years of 
separation sir henry and lady mary guildford are temporarily 
reunited in basel 
drawings of them are on display in the first joint showing of 
the worlds two most important collections of the graphic work of 
hans holbein the younger the basel burgher who became the court 
painter of henry viii 
the exhibit comprises 50 drawings from the collection of queen 
elizabeth ii on loan to the basel kunstmuseum and the 80 works 
normally on display at the museum 
an ancient wish has come true kunstmuseum director 
christian gelhaar said at the opening the exhibition of the 130 
works spans a career that made the germanborn holbein the first 
portrait painter to achieve international fame 
it ranges from a study for a doubleportrait of a basel mayor 
and his wife when he was 19 to a drawing of an english nobleman 
done shortly before the artist fell victim at the age of 46 to a 
plague sweeping london in 1543 
holbein a friend of the dutch scholar and humanist erasmus 
came to england in 1526 in search of lucrative orders because the 
arts were freezing in basel as erasmus put it 
erasmus sent him to sir thomas more the later chancellor who 
became holbeins first patron mores warning that holbein may 
not find england such fruitful and fertile land as he had hoped 
as he wrote erasmus was soon disproved 
portraits of henry guildford newlynamed treasurer of the crown 
by henry viii and his wife were among the key works holbein did 
during a first twoyear stay in england another was a more family 
portrait which has vanished 
returning to basel holbein took with him the studies for mores 
family portrait a gift for erasmus and for the portrait of lady 
mary the painting he did of her is now in missouri at the st 
louis art museum 
by that time holbein was wealthy enough to buy two houses in 
basel and received well paid commissions but iconoclastic riots by 
fanatic protestants boded ill for the future of an ambitious artist 
one of the victims was his altarpiece of the last supper which 
was chopped to pieces most of the fragments were salvaged 
however later joined together in an irregular way and even painted 
over at the exhibition the piece returns to public view after more 
than two decades of painstaking restoration 
in 1532 holbein made england his permanent home leaving behind 
his family and most of his oeuvre to become known according to an 
ancient english biographical note as the greatest master truly 
in the arts after the liffe that ever was 
the 50 drawings on loan through sept 4 from windsor castle 
make evident that this last period marked the culmination of his 
career as a portrait painter 
they impress visitors by the unerring way in which holbein 
captured the features of his subjects his sure sense of pattern 
and the proficiency with which the lefthanded artist worked with 
generous strokes of black and colored chalks 
a few show that even holbein had his offdays as jane roberts 
curator of the print room at windsor castle commented at the 
opening 
drawing an annual salary of 120 pounds sterling from the court 
he portrayed merchants scholars statesmen and mostly members of 
the court and nobility 
many of them were protagonists in a stormy period of english 
history that somewhat surprisingly seemed to leave holbein 
unperturbed the windsor collection includes drawings of anne 
boleyn the second wife of henry viii who was beheaded in 1536 of 
jane seymour the third wife as well of baron rich whose 
testimony led to the execution of thomas more 
no preparatory drawing of henry viii survived and what is rated 
as holbeins most masterful portrait of the monarch is in london 
on loan it is part of the lugano collection of baron heinrich von 
thyssenbornemisza which britain like other countries is bidding 
to be the permanent host 
</TEXT>
