but of the 2152 billion coupons distributed by companies to 
promote their products more than 208 billion went unused 
according to a study by manufacturers coupon control center which 
is a subsidiary of dun amp bradstreet corp 
slightly more than 3 percent of the total or 715 billion were 
redeemed which was a fraction ahead of 1986 the report said 
the lack of strong growth this year reflects a maturing 
industry the study said after several years of innovative 
marketing techniques including using coupons to introduce new 
products couponing has achieved a level of penetration that makes 
significant growth in the immediate future unlikely 
while the number of coupons redeemed leveled off their average 
value increased 14 percent to 397 cents from 376 cents the 
report said 
