year more than 2000 companies used coupons to promote their 
products and boost sales the report said during the same period 
the number of coupons redeemed grew by 29 percent 
newspaper inserts continued to be the most popular form of 
coupon distribution in 1987 while all other media forms except 
direct mail declined the report said 
grocery coupons inside and outside product packaging tended to 
be the most popular with consumers with a 14 percent and 13 
percent redemption rate respectively compared with other methods 
of distribution 
