cents a share to 1112 
cooper said it has enough cash flow to finance the company until 
the sale of one of its principal businesses but expects to 
complete within the next few weeks the previously announced 40 
million of bridge financing to help until the asset sales are 
completed 
the federal government last october blocked cibageigys 
proposed 150 million purchase of coopers worldwide contact lens 
and solutions businesses cooper wound up selling cibageigy only 
its international solutions business for 50 million 
earlier this year the government blocked scheringplough corp 
parent of contact lens maker wesleyjessen from buying coopers 
worldwide lens business for 150 million scheringplough also 
agreed to buy both coopers worldwide contact and us solutions 
businesses for 195 million but the government again blocked it on 
antitrust grounds 
